From: HVM <hvm@hellmessage.com>
Subject: [PATCH] meson: fix build on Darwin (no librt)

Darwin doesn't have librt — clock_gettime / aio etc. live in libSystem.
Stock spice-server 0.16.0 meson.build assumes non-Windows = Linux, fails
to find 'rt' shared library on macOS.

Skip 'rt' / 'm' dep search on darwin (libm is also part of libSystem).

Adapted from UTM PATCH 08/11 in spice-0.14.3.patch (osy 2022-03-04),
ported to spice-server 0.16.0 (line shifted from 102 to 109).

---
 meson.build | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/meson.build b/meson.build
index 0000000..0000001 100644
--- a/meson.build
+++ b/meson.build
@@ -106,7 +106,9 @@ foreach dep : ['libjpeg', 'zlib']
   spice_server_deps += dependency(dep)
 endforeach

-if host_machine.system() != 'windows'
+if host_machine.system() in ['darwin', 'ios']
+  # librt / libm not required on Darwin (provided by libSystem)
+elif host_machine.system() != 'windows'
   foreach dep : ['rt', 'm']
     spice_server_deps += compiler.find_library(dep)
   endforeach
